laboratory_examinations.findings: Bowel wall thickening involving the cecum and the proximal ascending colon with pericolonic fat stranding and small amount of free fluid, predominantly at the level of the cecum. The base of the appendix is dilated, measuring 10 mm. The distal portion of the appendix measures 6 mm. There are mesenteric and retroperitoneal lymph nodes, which do not meet CT criteria for pathologic enlargement.
